*DESCRIPTION*
Currently we are looking for an Android Developer for our San Francisco, CA office to make the team even stronger.
We are seeking an exceptionally talented person who has a passion for, takes pride in his/her work, and is perfectionist in what he/she does. We in turn can offer you a fast-paced working environment, a culture of mutual respect and teamwork along with a competitive remuneration. Those who like a good challenge and a daily dose of problem solving feel free to drop in for the details.
*RESPONSIBILITIES*
• Leading a team of 3-4 people;
• Making technical and architectural decisions;
• Closely working with business stakeholders;
• Coordinating between business and development;
• Helping the business with technical expertise, helping them making decisions.
*REQUIREMENTS*
• Experience in Android development;
• Experience in Java, App Components, UI frameworks, developer tools and workflows;
• Good understanding of Android Design Patterns, coding conventions as well as Google's Design Guidelines and Google Play Developer Program Policies;
• Good understanding of networking, caching of local data and multitasking on Android;
• Experience with 3rd party libraries and services;
• Experience with Agile processes;
• Leadership qualities, ability to work in a dynamic team environment, with a mix of local and remote resources;
• Development experience with other mobile platforms, a plus;
• Experience in HTML, CSS and JavaScript development skills, a plus;
• Very good communication skills.
